1. Login to gcloud
2. Create a new VM. for cheaper option - 
	a. take US server
	b. minimum storage 10gb
	c. any ISO - ubuntu
	d. External IP - ephemeral ( to keep it fixed even when VM is stopped)
3. Start the VM
4. Upgrade the linux installer --> apt-get ----- apt-get update
5. install apache2 --> apt-get install apache2
6. basic html can be checked at --> /var/www/.html
7. Create a new hostname (free for testing). You can use - freenom.com
8. configure External IP of VM to above domain.
